  "prompt": "Why do dogs chase people?",
  "response": "Dogs may chase people for several reasons:\n\n1. Predatory instinct\n- Some dogs have a natural prey drive\n- Movement can trigger their instinct to chase\n\n2. Territorial behavior\n- Protecting their home or property\n- Perceived threat to their space\n\n3. Playfulness\n- Some dogs want to play and think chasing is fun\n- Lacks understanding of human boundaries\n\n4. Fear or anxiety\n- Dogs might chase out of defensive response\n- Feeling threatened or scared\n\n5. Lack of training\n- Not taught proper socialization\n- No clear boundaries or obedience skills\n\n6. Breed characteristics\n- Some breeds are more prone to chasing\n- Herding dogs often have strong chase instincts\n\n7. Excitement\n- High energy dogs might chase from pure excitement\n- Overstimulation can trigger chasing behavior\n\n8. Medical issues\n- Certain health problems can affect behavior\n- Neurological conditions might cause compulsive chasing\n\nProper training, socialization, and understanding a dog's individual needs can help prevent unwanted chasing behavior.",
